					<div class="supermax-intro-copy">
						<p>Most responsive layouts handle narrow screens by stacking columns into one long page. That works for editorial content, but data-heavy applications often need a different rhythm: one focused pane on small screens, and as much useful context as possible when there is room.</p>
						<p>Supermax is built around that hybrid. On a phone, a layout can behave like an iOS-style navigation stack: move one step deeper, show one cell, and go back when needed. On a wider screen, those same cells sit side by side and grow up to their configured max widths.</p>
